race.description: Riverina Home Centre Stan Sadleir Stakes Handicap
race.comment: CANNY HELL (1) has been below his best in two runs back but has since been freshened with 48 days between. A dominant trial win suggests he's back on track and ready to tackle the longer journey. VILLASAURUS (3) resumes after five-and-a-half months and was sharp early last prep over this track and trip. Has been readied with two strong pieces of work and gets McDougall. BUENOS (7) flopped in Highway grade at Rosehill but her two wins prior showed class. Still learning and capable of bouncing back. Wide gate the only knock. FUTURE FUND (5) nearly made it two straight to kick off the prep. In great order and well placed down in the weights. Testing material. STUPENDO (9) deserves respect off his bold front-running win at Goulburn.
